    schema:courseSchedule <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000022/2025-26/eventSchedule> ;
    schema:description "This course presents the concepts of FAIR - Findability, Accessibility, Interoperability, and Reusability - as applied to scholarly data publishing. The FAIR Principles are discussed in detail, and then over a series of weeks a variety of technologies are taught and explored in a hands-on manner that provide technical solutions to each of the FAIR Principles."@es ;
